cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper discusses machine learning algorithms and their limitations in high-dimensional datasets, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on feature and variable selection also suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the mention of interpretability and CPU/memory resources suggests a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), where these issues are also relevant.
